column2: Step 1 PREP: Dice the tomato, chop the red pepper, onion, and turkey sausage. Step 2 In a large pan, drizzle onions and peppers with olive oil and saute. Step 3 When the onions are clear and peppers are tender, season with salt and pepper. Step 4 Add chopped turkey sausage, and saute until sausage is golden brown. Step 5 Lower heat, add egg whites, and scramble. Step 6 When eggs are almost done, add in tomato and spinach, mix around, and then serve. If your diet allows it, enjoy with a piece of whole grain toast for a complete and nutritious meal! (source: bodybuilding.com)
